cambium.name: cambium

revisions.description: PTP500-05-04: Added aAAControl group containing user table.
PTP500-05-03: Removed encryptionEnabledMismatchTrap. Renamed dfsChannelChangeTrap to channelChangeTrap.
PTP500-05-02: Corrected REVISION DESCRIPTION clause for 05-01.

PTP500-05-01: Updated ORGANIZATION and CONTACT-INFO. Replaced syslogLocalLog with syslogState. Added licensedCapacity and capacityLicenseMismatchTrap as part of SKU reduction. Added support for HTTPS. Added enabledDiagnosticAlarms attribute. Added support for syslog client. Removed lineOfSightModeInactive trap as part of SKU reduction (LOS no longer supported).
PTP500-04-01: Added latitude, longitude, altitude, searchState, accessMethod and groupID.
PTP500-04-00: Changed root OID. Added SNMPv3 support, TDD sync, DFS Table, BIT STRING types now OCTET STRING. Added linkName, siteName. Renamed ethernet attributes & traps.

ptpCompliance.name: ptpCompliance
ptpCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the Cambium PTP MIB

dfsTable.name: dfsTable
dfsTable.description: A table storing a snapshot of various DFS measurements for each channel

vLANPriorityTable.name: vLANPriorityTable
vLANPriorityTable.description: A priority queue mapping table. This is a list of packet queues indexed by VLAN priority.

userTable.name: userTable
userTable.description: The User Table Control group contains objects specifically for user account management.

dfsTableNumber.name: dfsTableNumber
dfsTableNumber.description: Number of entries in the dfsTable

dfsTableIndex.name: dfsTableIndex
dfsTableIndex.description: used to index values in the dfsTable.

iPAddress.name: iPAddress
iPAddress.description: Internet protocol (IP) address. This address is used by the family of Internet protocols to uniquely identify the unit on a network. NB: A system reboot is required to activate changes to this attribute.

subnetMask.name: subnetMask
subnetMask.description: A subnet allows the flow of network traffic between hosts to be segregated based on a network configuration. By organizing hosts into logical groups, subnetting can improve network security and performance. NB: A system reboot is required to activate changes to this attribute

gatewayIPAddress.name: gatewayIPAddress
gatewayIPAddress.description: The IP address of a computer on the current network that is currently acting as a network gateway. A gateway acts as an entrance / exit to packets from / to other networks. NB: A system reboot is required to activate changes to this attribute

targetMACAddress.name: targetMACAddress
targetMACAddress.description: MAC address of the PTP wireless unit forming the other end of the PTP link

masterSlaveMode.name: masterSlaveMode
masterSlaveMode.description: The PTP wireless link operates using a master and slave relationship

maximumTransmitPower.name: maximumTransmitPower
maximumTransmitPower.description: Maximum transmit power the wireless unit is permitted to use when establishing and maintaining the wireless link

antennaGain.name: antennaGain
antennaGain.description: Antenna Gain. Expressed in 10ths of dBi. NB: This attribute is ignored for variants with an integral antenna.

cableLoss.name: cableLoss
cableLoss.description: Loss in the cable between the ODU and the antenna. Expressed in 10ths of dB. NB: This attribute is ignored for variants with an integral antenna.

eIRP.name: eIRP
eIRP.description: Effective Isotropic Radiated Power (EIRP) describes the strength of the radio signal leaving the wireless unit. Expressed in 10ths of dBm

channelBandwidth.name: channelBandwidth
channelBandwidth.description: This control sets the bandwidth of the transmit and receive radio channels

remoteIPAddress.name: remoteIPAddress
remoteIPAddress.description: IP Address of the peer wireless unit

linkName.name: linkName
linkName.description: Name of the PTP link allocated by the System Administrator. Used to establish a connection with the correct PTP wireless unit at the other end of the link. NOTE: The link name MUST be the same at both ends of the PTP link.

siteName.name: siteName
siteName.description: This field contains a user-provided description of the site name together with any additional notes

accessMethod.name: accessMethod
accessMethod.description: This controls whether the link can be established between pre-paired Master-Slave using MAC addresses (Link Access) or by using link name (Link Name Access)

groupID.name: groupID
groupID.description: When Access Method is set to Group Access, the Group ID identifies all the units belonging to the same group. Group Access is only supported on some platforms

dataPortAutoNegotiation.name: dataPortAutoNegotiation
dataPortAutoNegotiation.description: This controls whether the local Ethernet interface configuration is automatically negotiated or forced. Do not use a forced setting together with auto negotiation at the Ethernet link partner. If you want to run your Ethernet link at a fixed speed and duplex then you would normally leave auto negotiation enabled and only enable the single Auto Neg Advertisement option that you want the link to run in - FORCING ETHERNET CONFIGURATION IS A LAST RESORT WHICH SHOULD ONLY BE PERFORMED IF YOU ARE HAVING PROBLEMS WITH AUTO NEGOTIATION - AND YOU MUST ENSURE THAT YOU CONFIGURE BOTH THIS UNIT AND THE ETHERNET LINK PARTNER TO WHICH IT IS CONNECTED IDENTICALLY (THE LINK PARTNER MUST NOT HAVE AUTO NEGOTIATION ENABLED EITHER, OTHERWISE A DUPLEX MISMATCH WILL OCCUR). NB: The new setting will only take effect after a system reboot.

dataPortAutoNegAdvertisement.name: dataPortAutoNegAdvertisement
dataPortAutoNegAdvertisement.description: This sets the different Ethernet configurations that will be advertised during auto negotiation. NB: The new setting will only take effect after a system reboot. WARNING: Duplex mismatch may result if both ends of the Ethernet link do not have the same settings. Do not auto negotiation together with a fixed setting at the Ethernet link partner. WARNING: Make sure that you select option(s) that you know your connected equipment can cater for!

dataPortAutoMdix.name: dataPortAutoMdix
dataPortAutoMdix.description: This enables/disables the Auto MDI/MDIX capability. NB: The new setting will only take effect after a system reboot

dataPortStatus.name: dataPortStatus
dataPortStatus.description: Current status of the Ethernet link. NB: a change of state may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

dataPortSpeedAndDuplex.name: dataPortSpeedAndDuplex
dataPortSpeedAndDuplex.description: The current speed and duplex of the Ethernet link

dataPortWirelessDownAlert.name: dataPortWirelessDownAlert
dataPortWirelessDownAlert.description: When enabled, this causes the Ethernet link to be dropped briefly when the wireless link drops. This is so that spanning tree algorithms can quickly detect that there is a problem.

useVLANForManagementInterfaces.name: useVLANForManagementInterfaces
useVLANForManagementInterfaces.description: This controls whether the management interfaces (WWW/SNMP/SMTP/SNTP) use VLAN tags or not. NB: The new setting will only take effect after a system reboot

vLANManagementPriority.name: vLANManagementPriority
vLANManagementPriority.description: This VLAN Priority (0-7) will be included in packets generated by the management interfaces. NB: The new setting will only take effect after a system reboot

vLANManagementVID.name: vLANManagementVID
vLANManagementVID.description: This VLAN VID (0-4094) will be included in packets generated by the management interfaces. NB: The new setting will only take effect after a system reboot

vLANPriorityTableNumber.name: vLANPriorityTableNumber
vLANPriorityTableNumber.description: Number of entries in the vLANPriorityTable.

vLANPriorityQueueMapping.name: vLANPriorityQueueMapping
vLANPriorityQueueMapping.description: Mapping of VLAN priority flag to packet queue. The higher the queue number the greater its priority.

vLANPriorityTableIndex.name: vLANPriorityTableIndex
vLANPriorityTableIndex.description: VLAN priority flag, used to index values in the vLANPriorityTable.

telecomsInterface.name: telecomsInterface
telecomsInterface.description: The line interface type. If this is set to 'None' then the telecoms interfaces are disabled, and the telecom group attributes will be ignored.

telecomsChannelStatus.name: telecomsChannelStatus
telecomsChannelStatus.description: Current status of telecoms channel. NB: a change of state may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

telecomsLineCode.name: telecomsLineCode
telecomsLineCode.description: The line code setting of the telecoms interface. This must match the setting of the device connected to this interface

telecomsCableLength.name: telecomsCableLength
telecomsCableLength.description: The length of the cable connected to the telecoms interface, measured in feet

telecomsLoopback.name: telecomsLoopback
telecomsLoopback.description: The loopback status of telecoms channel. This is intended for installation testing and should be set to 'None' for normal operation. The wire connections to a unit can be tested by applying a 'Copper' loopback to the local unit. The wireless connection to the remote unit can be tested by applying a 'Wireless' loopback to the remote unit with no loopback on the local unit. When applying a wireless loopback, please ensure that the other end of the link has a loopback setting of 'None'. NB: a change of state may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

regionCode.name: regionCode
regionCode.description: The region code prohibits the wireless unit from operating outside the regulated limits. An invalid region code indicates a corrupted licence key. NB: a change of state may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

ethernetFiberSupport.name: ethernetFiberSupport
ethernetFiberSupport.description: Ethernet fiber support availability on this wireless unit

frequencyVariant.name: frequencyVariant
frequencyVariant.description: Frequency variant of the wireless unit

bandwidthVariant.name: bandwidthVariant
bandwidthVariant.description: Bandwidth variant of the wireless unit

constantPowerSpectralDensity.name: constantPowerSpectralDensity
constantPowerSpectralDensity.description: Constant power spectral density mode control

licensedCapacity.name: licensedCapacity
licensedCapacity.description: Maximum allowable data rate for ethernet frames permitted by the licence key. The actual data rate depends upon the prevailing wireless conditions

installStatus.name: installStatus
installStatus.description: A non-zero value indicates that signalling was received with the wrong MAC address or a mismatched link name. NB: It is very unusual to detect this, because units with mis-configured Target MAC Address will normally fail to establish a wireless link. However, rare circumstances may establish a partial wireless link and detect this situation. NB: A non-zero value on start-up, or a change of value during operation, may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

installArmState.name: installArmState
installArmState.description: Indicates if the unit is being installed. NB: a value other than 'disarmed' on startup, or a change of state during operation may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

tFTPServerIPAddress.name: tFTPServerIPAddress
tFTPServerIPAddress.description: IP address of the TFTP Server from which the TFTP Software Upgrade File Name will be retrieved

tFTPServerPortNumber.name: tFTPServerPortNumber
tFTPServerPortNumber.description: The port number of the TFTP Server from which the TFTP Software Upgrade File Name will be retrieved

tFTPSoftwareUpgradeFileName.name: tFTPSoftwareUpgradeFileName
tFTPSoftwareUpgradeFileName.description: Filename of the Software Upgrade to be loaded from the TFTP Server

tFTPStartSoftwareUpgrade.name: tFTPStartSoftwareUpgrade
tFTPStartSoftwareUpgrade.description: Write '1' to this attribute to start the TFTP software upgrade process. The attribute will be reset to 0 when the upgrade process has finished

tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatus.name: tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatus
tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatus.description: The current status of the TFTP Software upgrade process

tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatusText.name: tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatusText
tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatusText.description: Descriptive text describing the status of the TFTP Software upgrade process, including any error details

tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatusAdditionalText.name: tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatusAdditionalText
tFTPSoftwareUpgradeStatusAdditionalText.description: Any additional text describing the status of the TFTP Software upgrade process, including any error details

hTTPAccessEnabled.name: hTTPAccessEnabled
hTTPAccessEnabled.description: This controls whether or not HTTP access is enabled, i.e. if this is disabled (0) then the unit will not respond to any requests on the HTTP port. Remote management via HTTPS is not affected by this setting. Any change in this setting will not take effect until the unit has been rebooted. (Factory default = Enabled)

telnetAccessEnabled.name: telnetAccessEnabled
telnetAccessEnabled.description: This controls whether or not Telnet access is enabled, i.e. if this is disabled (0) then the unit will not respond to any requests on the TELNET port. Any change in this setting will not take effect until the unit has been rebooted. (Factory default = Disabled)

hTTPPortNumber.name: hTTPPortNumber
hTTPPortNumber.description: This controls the port number for HTTP access. A value of zero will use the default port number. Any change in this setting will not take effect until the unit has been rebooted. (Factory default = 80)

hTTPSPortNumber.name: hTTPSPortNumber
hTTPSPortNumber.description: This controls the port number for HTTPS access. A value of zero will use the default port number. Availability of HTTPS is controlled via the Licence Key. Any change in this setting will not take effect until the unit has been rebooted. (Factory default = 443)

telnetPortNumber.name: telnetPortNumber
telnetPortNumber.description: This controls the port number for TELNET access. A value of zero will use the default port number. Any change in this setting will not take effect until the unit has been rebooted. (Factory default = 23)

hTTPSAccessEnabled.name: hTTPSAccessEnabled
hTTPSAccessEnabled.description: This controls whether or not HTTPS access is enabled, i.e. if this is disabled (0) then the unit will not respond to any requests on the HTTPS port. Remote management via HTTP is not affected by this setting. Any change in this setting will not take effect until the unit has been rebooted. (Factory default = Enabled)

linkSymmetry.name: linkSymmetry
linkSymmetry.description: In fixed asymmetric mode (3 to 1) the transmit time is three times as long as the receive time. In fixed symmetric mode (1 to 1) the unit spends an equal amount of time transmitting and receiving. In fixed asymmetric mode (1 to 3) the receive time is three times as long as the transmit time. In adaptive mode the transmit and receive periods adjust with applied load. NB: only applicable for master nodes.

linkModeOptimisation.name: linkModeOptimisation
linkModeOptimisation.description: Optimises the wireless link behavior for the type of traffic to be carried. In 'IP Traffic' mode, the wireless link will minimise transmission errors by automatically adapting the modulation mode. In 'TDM Traffic' mode, the wireless link will minimise transmission latency and preserve throughput by maintaining a higher modulation mode in the presence of a limited number of errors. The 'TDM Traffic' mode is recommended for E1/T1 applications and connectionless protocols.

userConfiguredMaxModulationMode.name: userConfiguredMaxModulationMode
userConfiguredMaxModulationMode.description: The maximum receive modulation mode controls the MAX mode used for adaptive modulation. NOTE: This attribute is automatically disabled when the installation agent is armed. To disarm the installation agent use the installation wizard

remoteMaximumTransmitPower.name: remoteMaximumTransmitPower
remoteMaximumTransmitPower.description: Maximum transmit power the remote wireless unit is permitted to use when establishing and maintaining the wireless link

receivePower.name: receivePower
receivePower.description: Receive power expressed in tenths of a dBm

vectorError.name: vectorError
vectorError.description: The vector error measurement compares the received signal's IQ modulation characteristics to an ideal signal to determine the composite error vector magnitude. The value represented by this attribute is the average vector error over the previous second expressed in tenths of a dB

transmitPower.name: transmitPower
transmitPower.description: Transmit power expressed in tenths of a dBm

range.name: range
range.description: Distance between the two peer wireless units expressed in tenths of a kilometer

linkLoss.name: linkLoss
linkLoss.description: The wireless link loss expressed in tenths of a dB

receiveFreqMHz.name: receiveFreqMHz
receiveFreqMHz.description: Current receive frequency expressed in integer MHz

transmitFreqMHz.name: transmitFreqMHz
transmitFreqMHz.description: Current transmit frequency expressed in integer MHz

signalStrengthRatio.name: signalStrengthRatio
signalStrengthRatio.description: Signal strength ratio (Vertical / Horizontal) : the number of dB larger the Vertical antenna input is than the Horizontal antenna input expressed in tenths of a dB

receiveFreqKHz.name: receiveFreqKHz
receiveFreqKHz.description: Current receive frequency expressed as KHz

transmitFreqKHz.name: transmitFreqKHz
transmitFreqKHz.description: Current transmit frequency expressed as KHz

searchState.name: searchState
searchState.description: Search status of the wireless modem. 'Registering' means that the modem has locked to an OFDM signal, and the wireless link is up. 'Searching' means that no wireless signal has been detected. 'Acquiring' means that a wireless signal has been detected, but the modem has not locked to an OFDM signal.

unitOutOfCalibration.name: unitOutOfCalibration
unitOutOfCalibration.description: The unit is out of calibration

incompatibleRegionCodes.name: incompatibleRegionCodes
incompatibleRegionCodes.description: The master and slave units have incompatible region codes. NB: Both units must have compatible licence keys

noWirelessChannelAvailable.name: noWirelessChannelAvailable
noWirelessChannelAvailable.description: Spectrum Management was unable to locate a suitable wireless channel to operate on

wirelessLinkDisabledWarning.name: wirelessLinkDisabledWarning
wirelessLinkDisabledWarning.description: The SNMP ifAdminStatus of the wireless interface has disabled wireless traffic

dataPortDisabledWarning.name: dataPortDisabledWarning
dataPortDisabledWarning.description: The SNMP ifAdminStatus of the Ethernet interface has disabled Ethernet traffic

dataPortConfigurationMismatch.name: dataPortConfigurationMismatch
dataPortConfigurationMismatch.description: The detection of Ethernet fragments (runt packets) when the link is in full duplex is an indication of an auto-negotiation or forced configuration mismatch

incompatibleMasterAndSlave.name: incompatibleMasterAndSlave
incompatibleMasterAndSlave.description: A non-zero value indicates that the master and slave ends of a link are different hardware products, or have different software versions. NB: It is very unusual to detect this, because incompatible units will normally fail to establish a wireless link. However, some combinations may establish a partial wireless link and detect this situation. NB: A non-zero value may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

tDDSynchronizationStatus.name: tDDSynchronizationStatus
tDDSynchronizationStatus.description: An alarm value (displayed in red) indicates that one of the following conditions has not been met (i) An external timing system is connected or internal timing has been configured. (ii) The timing system is providing a useable reference. (iii) The ODU is locked to this reference.

tDDSynchronizationAlarm.name: tDDSynchronizationAlarm
tDDSynchronizationAlarm.description: Not Synchronized indicates failure of the external timing system for a period greater than the holdover timer. TDD frame timing will have drifted, and this link may cause interference with other links in a synchronized network. Timing System Failure is an early warning, indicating that 80% of the holdover period has expired.

linkModeOptimizationMismatch.name: linkModeOptimizationMismatch
linkModeOptimizationMismatch.description: The remote node of this link has been configured with a different link mode optimization

capacityLicenseMismatch.name: capacityLicenseMismatch
capacityLicenseMismatch.description: The local and remote units have different licensed capacity and/or the full capacity trial has been activated at only one unit. The wireless link is operating at the capacity of the lowest capacity unit

sMTPEmailAlert.name: sMTPEmailAlert
sMTPEmailAlert.description: Simple Mail Transfer Protocol is used to send equipment alerts via email to a specified email address. This utility can only be configured by the system administrator

sMTPServerIPAddress.name: sMTPServerIPAddress
sMTPServerIPAddress.description: IP address of the SMTP server

sMTPServerPortNumber.name: sMTPServerPortNumber
sMTPServerPortNumber.description: Port number of the SMTP server

sMTPSourceEmailAddress.name: sMTPSourceEmailAddress
sMTPSourceEmailAddress.description: The 'from' email address used when constructing the automatically generated e-mail message

sMTPDestinationEmailAddress.name: sMTPDestinationEmailAddress
sMTPDestinationEmailAddress.description: The 'to' email address used when constructing the automatically generated e-mail message

sMTPEnabledMessages.name: sMTPEnabledMessages
sMTPEnabledMessages.description: This controls which SMTP messages the unit will send

sNMPPortNumber.name: sNMPPortNumber
sNMPPortNumber.description: The IP port number used to access the SNMP MIB (i.e. Gets and Sets) (default = 161). NB: A system reboot is required to activate changes to this attribute

sNMPCommunityString.name: sNMPCommunityString
sNMPCommunityString.description: The SNMP community string. NB: A system reboot is required to activate changes to this attribute

sNMPTrapTableNumber.name: sNMPTrapTableNumber
sNMPTrapTableNumber.description: Number of entries in the sNMPTrapTable.

sNMPTrapVersion.name: sNMPTrapVersion
sNMPTrapVersion.description: The SNMP protocol version to use for SNMP Traps. NB: A system reboot is required to activate changes to this attribute

sNMPEnabledTraps.name: sNMPEnabledTraps
sNMPEnabledTraps.description: This controls which SNMP Traps the unit will send

enabledDiagnosticAlarms.name: enabledDiagnosticAlarms
enabledDiagnosticAlarms.description: Controls which individual diagnostic alarms are enabled. The unit may be configured to generate SNMP traps and/or SMTP email alerts for these enabled alarms by selecting 'Enabled Diagnostic Alarms' on the 'SNMP Enabled Traps' and/or 'SMTP Enabled Messages' attributes

sNMPSendAllTrapsAtStartup.name: sNMPSendAllTrapsAtStartup
sNMPSendAllTrapsAtStartup.description: Controls whether cleared traps are reported at start-up as well as raised traps. Only enabled traps will be reported. NB: Traps corresponding to transient events (i.e. not associated with an alarm or status value) are only sent when required and not at start-up.

sNMPTrapTableIndex.name: sNMPTrapTableIndex
sNMPTrapTableIndex.description: SNMP trap value, used to index the SNMPTrapTable.

sNMPTrapIPAddress.name: sNMPTrapIPAddress
sNMPTrapIPAddress.description: The IP address to which all SNMP Traps are sent. An IP Address of 0.0.0.0 disables all TRAP generation. NB: A system reboot is required to activate changes to this attribute.

sNMPTrapPortNumber.name: sNMPTrapPortNumber
sNMPTrapPortNumber.description: Destination port for SNMP Traps (default=162). A value of 0 will disable the trap receiver. NB: A system reboot is required to activate changes to this attribute.

sNTPServerIPAddress.name: sNTPServerIPAddress
sNTPServerIPAddress.description: The IP address of a valid SNTP server

sNTPServerPortNumber.name: sNTPServerPortNumber
sNTPServerPortNumber.description: The IP port number of the SNTP server. Defaults to port 123.

sNTPSync.name: sNTPSync
sNTPSync.description: If SNTP Sync fails then check the server settings in the Remote Management page, or disable SNTP. NB: a change of state may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

systemClock.name: systemClock
systemClock.description: System clock presented as local time

timeZone.name: timeZone
timeZone.description: Time zone offsets from Greenwich Mean Time (GMT)

systemReset.name: systemReset
systemReset.description: Setting this attribute to '1' will cause a system reboot. NB: a system reboot will apply any pending new settings held in memory

secondarySoftwareVersion.name: secondarySoftwareVersion
secondarySoftwareVersion.description: Secondary software version, used when the primary software image is invalid or erased

receiveDataRate.name: receiveDataRate
receiveDataRate.description: Average data rate over the last one second interval (kbps)

transmitDataRate.name: transmitDataRate
transmitDataRate.description: Average data rate over the last one second interval (kbps)

aggregateDataRate.name: aggregateDataRate
aggregateDataRate.description: Average data rate over the last one second interval (kbps)

wirelessLinkAvailability.name: wirelessLinkAvailability
wirelessLinkAvailability.description: Link availability calculated since the last reset of the system counters, as a percentage multiplied by 10000 to give four decimal places of precision

wirelessLinkStatus.name: wirelessLinkStatus
wirelessLinkStatus.description: Current status of the wireless link

byteErrorRatio.name: byteErrorRatio
byteErrorRatio.description: Reciprocal of the byte error ratio calculated since the last reset of the system counters

receiveModulationModeDetail.name: receiveModulationModeDetail
receiveModulationModeDetail.description: The reason for the current receive modulation mode

encryptionAlgorithm.name: encryptionAlgorithm
encryptionAlgorithm.description: The Encryption Algorithm used by the wireless link. NB: A system reboot is required to activate changes to this attribute. NB: The same Encryption Algorithm must be configured at BOTH ends of the link for it to function correctly

userTableNumber.name: userTableNumber
userTableNumber.description: Number of entries in the userTable

userTableIndex.name: userTableIndex
userTableIndex.description: used to index values in the userTable.

userName.name: userName
userName.description: User name which must be entered, along with the appropriate password, in order to gain access to the system.

userRole.name: userRole
userRole.description: Role of the selected user. A Security Officer has access to and can modify all settings. A System Administrator has access to and can modify all non-security settings. A Read Only user can view settings, but cannot make any changes.

userPassword.name: userPassword
userPassword.description: User password, which must be entered in order to gain access to the system.

syslogClient.name: syslogClient
syslogClient.description: Enable or disable the syslog client

syslogState.name: syslogState
syslogState.description: The syslog service has been enabled or disabled

longitude.name: longitude
longitude.description: The longitude of the unit, measured in decimal degrees. This object is set by the SNMP manager and has no internal function.

latitude.name: latitude
latitude.description: The latitude of the unit, measured in decimal degrees. This object is set by the SNMP manager and has no internal function.

altitude.name: altitude
altitude.description: The altitude of the unit, measured in metres. This object is set by the SNMP manager and has no internal function.

channelChangeTrap.name: channelChangeTrap
channelChangeTrap.description: The PTP radio has changed wireless channel. This has been caused by either i) mandatory radar avoidance, a DFS impulsive interference event will also be detected, or ii) Dynamic Spectrum Optimization, (DSO) DSO improves link performance by selecting the most appropriate transmit and receive channels with the lowest level of interference.

dataPortStatusTrap.name: dataPortStatusTrap
dataPortStatusTrap.description: Current status of the Ethernet link. NB: a change of state may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

telecomsChannelStatusTrap.name: telecomsChannelStatusTrap
telecomsChannelStatusTrap.description: Current status of telecoms channel. NB: a change of state may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

telecomsLoopbackTrap.name: telecomsLoopbackTrap
telecomsLoopbackTrap.description: The loopback status of telecoms channel. This is intended for installation testing and should be set to 'None' for normal operation. The wire connections to a unit can be tested by applying a 'Copper' loopback to the local unit. The wireless connection to the remote unit can be tested by applying a 'Wireless' loopback to the remote unit with no loopback on the local unit. When applying a wireless loopback, please ensure that the other end of the link has a loopback setting of 'None'. NB: a change of state may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

regionCodeTrap.name: regionCodeTrap
regionCodeTrap.description: The region code prohibits the wireless unit from operating outside the regulated limits. An invalid region code indicates a corrupted licence key. NB: a change of state may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

installStatusTrap.name: installStatusTrap
installStatusTrap.description: A non-zero value indicates that signalling was received with the wrong MAC address or a mismatched link name. NB: It is very unusual to detect this, because units with mis-configured Target MAC Address will normally fail to establish a wireless link. However, rare circumstances may establish a partial wireless link and detect this situation. NB: A non-zero value on start-up, or a change of value during operation, may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

installArmStateTrap.name: installArmStateTrap
installArmStateTrap.description: Indicates if the unit is being installed. NB: a value other than 'disarmed' on startup, or a change of state during operation may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

unitOutOfCalibrationTrap.name: unitOutOfCalibrationTrap
unitOutOfCalibrationTrap.description: The unit is out of calibration

incompatibleRegionCodesTrap.name: incompatibleRegionCodesTrap
incompatibleRegionCodesTrap.description: The master and slave units have incompatible region codes. NB: Both units must have compatible licence keys

noWirelessChannelAvailableTrap.name: noWirelessChannelAvailableTrap
noWirelessChannelAvailableTrap.description: Spectrum Management was unable to locate a suitable wireless channel to operate on

wirelessLinkDisabledWarningTrap.name: wirelessLinkDisabledWarningTrap
wirelessLinkDisabledWarningTrap.description: The SNMP ifAdminStatus of the wireless interface has disabled wireless traffic

dataPortDisabledWarningTrap.name: dataPortDisabledWarningTrap
dataPortDisabledWarningTrap.description: The SNMP ifAdminStatus of the Ethernet interface has disabled Ethernet traffic

dataPortConfigurationMismatchTrap.name: dataPortConfigurationMismatchTrap
dataPortConfigurationMismatchTrap.description: The detection of Ethernet fragments (runt packets) when the link is in full duplex is an indication of an auto-negotiation or forced configuration mismatch

incompatibleMasterAndSlaveTrap.name: incompatibleMasterAndSlaveTrap
incompatibleMasterAndSlaveTrap.description: A non-zero value indicates that the master and slave ends of a link are different hardware products, or have different software versions. NB: It is very unusual to detect this, because incompatible units will normally fail to establish a wireless link. However, some combinations may establish a partial wireless link and detect this situation. NB: A non-zero value may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

sNTPSyncTrap.name: sNTPSyncTrap
sNTPSyncTrap.description: If SNTP Sync fails then check the server settings in the Remote Management page, or disable SNTP. NB: a change of state may generate an SNMP trap and/or SMTP email alert

tDDSynchronizationAlarmTrap.name: tDDSynchronizationAlarmTrap
tDDSynchronizationAlarmTrap.description: Not Synchronized indicates failure of the external timing system for a period greater than the holdover timer. TDD frame timing will have drifted, and this link may cause interference with other links in a synchronized network. Timing System Failure is an early warning, indicating that 80% of the holdover period has expired.
